oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Christian Brothers College: Elocution Contest (Juniors)
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Programs; Contests
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Several students competed in the Elocution Contest for the junior class members of 1903: George Dichtel, Thomas Morriss, Oscar Wynn, Cornelius Clancy, John J. Shea, Charles Wallace, Henry Waring, Edward Herbers, William Fay, and Philip Canale. The contest was held at the Young Men's Hebrew Association Hall, which was located at Second and Union in downtown Memphis.
